comments.body:
> [a2a2bd7](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/29256/changes/a2a2bd7898a2dd190f83a248dda97dd726f91b0a) _log refactor: Add support for custom log sources_:

Might be cleaner to have these as a local lambda and type that cleanly just executes a lambda, instead of having to know about the exact test implementation, e.g.
```C++
using Fmt1 = util::ConstevalFormatString<1>;
struct CustomLogSource : util::log::Source {
    using LogFormatter = std::function<std::string(Fmt1, const char*)>;
    LogFormatter m_fmt;
    explicit CustomLogSource(BCLog::LogFlags s, LogFormatter fmt) : Source{s}, m_fmt{std::move(fmt)} {}
    std::string Format(Fmt1 fmt, const char* arg) const { return m_fmt(fmt, arg); }
};

int counter{0};
auto log = CustomLogSource{BCLog::VALIDATION, [&counter](Fmt1 fmt, const char* arg) {
    return tfm::format("Custom #%d %s", ++counter, tfm::format(fmt, arg));
}};
```

nit1: `public` is implicit
nit2: `explicit` is not implicit :p

